<HL>
   Greiner Gets Airport Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
05/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST GII
</CO>
<IN>
HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Greiner Engineering Inc. said it signed a
contract with the government of Hong Kong to serve as
planning and engineering consultant for the development of a
$4.1 billion airport in Hong Kong. The planning and design of
the project will proceed on an accelerated schedule so the
facility can open in early 1997, the engineering and
architectural services firm said. Terms of the contract
weren't disclosed.
</LP>
