   DALLAS -- Metro Airlines said its April traffic rose 42%,
to 52.4 million revenue passenger miles from 37 million in
the year-earlier period.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Load factor, or the percentage of seats filled, increased
to 54.8% from 48.9%.
   For the year to date, Metro flew 188.3 million revenue
passenger miles, a 47% increase from 128.4 million a year
ago. Load factor increased to 51.5% from 48% last year.
