<HL>
   Spain's Tourism Revenue
</HL>
<DATE>
05/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   MADRID -- Spain's tourism revenue dropped 3.2% in the
first three months of the year to 363.9 billion pesetas
($3.51 billion) from 375.9 billion pesetas ($3.62 billion) a
year earlier, according to the Ministry of Transportation,
Tourism and Communication.
   Tourism, which accounts for nearly 10% of Spain's gross
domestic product, has sagged in recent months after booming
in 1987 and 1988 and stabilizing in 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Last year, revenue from tourism reached $16.1 billion.
</TEXT>
