<HL>
   China's Industrial Output Rises
</HL>
<DATE>
05/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A19
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   BEIJING -- Chinese industrial production picked up in
April after a stagnant first quarter, with a 6.8% increase in
output over March, the State Statistical Bureau announced
yesterday.
   Compared with April 1989, however, this April's output of
164.6 billion renmimbi ($34.87 billion) was up only 2%, the
official Xinhua News Agency quoted bureau officials as
saying.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Chinese industry is reeling from the impact of a
government austerity program that sharply cut official
spending, new construction and loans. More than 3 million
small rural factories shut down and numerous urban factories
either closed or sharply cut production.
</TEXT>
